  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Computers and English language as a way to develop children and adults</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="SK">Po&#x10D;&#xED;ta&#x10D;e a anglick&#xFD; jazyk ako cesta k rozvoju det&#xED; i dospel&#xFD;ch</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="SK">Dobrovo&#x13E;n&#xED;k sa bude s&#xFA;stre&#x10F;ova&#x165; na pr&#xE1;cu so zamestnancami rozvojov&#xE9;ho oddelenia diec&#xE9;zy, najm&#xE4; &#x10D;o sa t&#xFD;ka znalosti pr&#xE1;ce s po&#x10D;&#xED;ta&#x10D;mi a anglick&#xE9;ho jazyka. V prvej f&#xE1;ze pobytu zrealizuje anal&#xFD;zu ich vedomost&#xED; a konkr&#xE9;tnych potrieb (hovoren&#xE1; / p&#xED;somn&#xE1; komunik&#xE1;cia v anglickom jazyku, porozumenie, MS Windows, MS Word, Excel, PowerPoint, vyh&#x13E;ad&#xE1;vanie inform&#xE1;ci&#xED; na internete a pod) a na ich z&#xE1;klade priprav&#xED; individu&#xE1;lny a skupinov&#xFD; harmonogram tr&#xE9;ningov a konzult&#xE1;ci&#xED;.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Volunteer will focus on working with staff of the development department of the diocese, particularly with regard to computer skills and English language - spoken / written communication in the English language, comprehension, MS Windows, MS Word, Excel, PowerPoint, finding information on the Internet, etc. and on that basis, prepare individual and group training schedule and consultation.</narrative>
  </description>
